		<h2 id="were-all-in-this-together">We’re all in this together</h2>
		
		<p>We hold ourselves to the same standard of transparency that we aim to achieve for the immigration detention network, and believe that our methods are improved by being public. Our methodology for processing data will be published with each dataset we analyse. We will also publish our processes for investigation, data processing and publish, as we have drawn on what others have published in turn. </p>
		
		<p>Our mission and methods are drawn from the ideas of pioneering organisations and individuals. Credit should be given where it is due. Our major influences include Wikileaks, Pro Publica, Heather Brooke, Clay Shirky, Open Australia, Edward Tufte, Jeremy Keith, Robert Rosenthal, </p>
		
